  "title": "The RangeSlider doesnt seem to adhere to the given precision for the halfway point",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nIf we pass a `precision` of 0 to the range slider (and a `step` of 1) I would expect that the halfway point would be a whole number. But the halfway indicator isn't rounded (somewhere around `computeDefaultPitPoints`)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1492861/50012096-0d7d8880-ffbe-11e8-9bd0-0ef2c356a7e3.png)\r\n\r\nThis is a yearly slider where i would have expected either 2003 or 2004 halfway.. :)\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\n1. Add a rangeSlider widget from the correct index without any furter configuration (since the defaults should be a precision of 0 and step can even be neglegted)\r\n4. See error\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nI guess some sort of whole number would be nice :) Or an option to manipulate the exact presentation?\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - Version 2.10.4 of instantsearch.js\r\n\r\nThanks!",
